.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH nofs 1  "nofs 0.1.7" 
.SH NAME
nofs \- A lightweight shared filesystem tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBnofs\fR [\fB\-c\fR|\fB\-\-config\fR] [\fB\-\-paths\fR] [\fB\-\-policy\fR] [\fB\-\-minfreespace\fR] [\fB\-v\fR|\fB\-\-verbose\fR] [\fB\-\-json\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
A lightweight shared filesystem tool
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version
.SH CONFIGURATION
.TP
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-config\fR \fI<CONFIG>\fR
Path to configuration file
.TP
\fB\-\-paths\fR \fI<PATHS>\fR
Comma\-separated list of branch paths (ad\-hoc mode) Format: /path1,/path2 or /path1=RW,/path2=RO
.SH POLICY
.TP
\fB\-\-policy\fR \fI<POLICY>\fR [default: pfrd]
Policy to use for branch selection
.TP
\fB\-\-minfreespace\fR \fI<MINFREESPACE>\fR [default: 4G]
Minimum free space required on branch (e.g., "4G", "100M")
.SH OUTPUT
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Verbose output (print decision steps to stderr)
.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Output in JSON format (for scripting/automation)
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
nofs\-ls(1)
List directory contents (like ls)
.TP
nofs\-find(1)
Find files matching a pattern
.TP
nofs\-which(1)
Find which branch contains a file
.TP
nofs\-create(1)
Get the best branch path for creating a new file
.TP
nofs\-stat(1)
Show filesystem statistics
.TP
nofs\-info(1)
Show share configuration and status
.TP
nofs\-exists(1)
Check if a file exists and return its location
.TP
nofs\-cat(1)
Read file content (from first found branch)
.TP
nofs\-cp(1)
Copy files/directories (supports nofs context paths)
.TP
nofs\-mv(1)
Move files/directories (supports nofs context paths)
.TP
nofs\-rm(1)
Remove files or directories
.TP
nofs\-mkdir(1)
Create directories
.TP
nofs\-rmdir(1)
Remove empty directories
.TP
nofs\-touch(1)
Create or update files
.TP
nofs\-du(1)
Show disk usage (recursive directory size calculation)
.TP
nofs\-completions(1)
Generate shell completion scripts
.TP
nofs\-manpage(1)
Generate man pages
.TP
nofs\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
.SH VERSION
v0.1.7
